  <steps>
    <step num="0">In a medium bowl, combine chocolate chips and condensed milk. </step>
    <step num="1">Microwave for 1 minute and mix together until smooth. </step>
    <step num="2">Lay a piece of parchment paper over a 9x9-inch (23x23-cm) baking dish. </step>
    <step num="3">Transfer chocolate mix to baking dish, spread evenly. </step>
    <step num="4">Refrigerate for 10 minutes. </step>
    <step num="5">Spread peanut butter evenly over the top of the cooled fudge. </step>
